This paper deals with image classification, which is a core problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the impact of noise on classification performance, which is a common problem in machine learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses denoising methods to mitigate the effects of noise, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of feature extraction methods such as LBP and HOG, which are commonly used in image processing and computer vision, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well.
